# Release Versioning Checklist

When creating a release, hotfix, or bumping version numbers, follow this checklist.

## 1. Bump Palace version numbers

In `Palace.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`:
- `MARKETING_VERSION` — semver release version (e.g., `2.2.1`)
- `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION` — monotonically increasing build number (e.g., `429`)

All 4 build configurations (Palace Debug, Palace Release, Palace+DRM Debug, Palace+DRM Release) must match.

## 2. Tag all submodules

Every release MUST tag its submodules so hotfixes can revert to the exact dependency versions. The `ios-audiobooktoolkit` submodule is the most critical — it has no independent versioning and must be tagged from ios-core.

```bash
# Tag audiobooktoolkit at whatever commit the submodule points to
cd ios-audiobooktoolkit
git tag -a "<PALACE_VERSION>" $(git rev-parse HEAD) -m "Palace <PALACE_VERSION> release"
git push origin --tags
cd ..
```

Tags should match the Palace `MARKETING_VERSION` (e.g., `2.2.1`).

## 3. Hotfix submodule alignment

For hotfixes based on an older release, revert submodules to their tagged version:

```bash
cd ios-audiobooktoolkit
git checkout <TARGET_RELEASE_TAG>  # e.g., git checkout 2.0.0
cd ..
git add ios-audiobooktoolkit
git commit -m "Revert audiobooktoolkit to <TAG> for hotfix"
```

